    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_682473360" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/682473360" />
    <a title="The American Conservative" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11859986-the-american-conservative"><img alt="The American Conservative" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1369778720p2/11859986.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/682473360?book_show_action=true">Jul 31, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The American Conservative" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The American Conservative" href="/user/show/11859986-the-american-conservative">The American Conservative</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780743291583" href="/book/show/2485978.Farm_Sanctuary">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer682473360" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1858757746320869784">&apos;What Baur and those like him want is hardly radical. In fact, it’s perfectly sane, even modest: a return to a morally responsible standard of animal husbandry. “The animal protection cause simply asks that animals not be treated like things but respected as creatures with inherent rights,” he writes. “It also maintains that we have an ethical responsibility not to abuse them.”&apos;<br/><br/>Read the full review, &quot;The Conscience of a Carnivore,&quot; on our website:<br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.theamericanconservative.com/articles/the-conscience-of-a-carnivore/'>http://www.theamericanconservative.co...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText1858757746320869784" style="display:none">'What Baur and those like him want is hardly radical. In fact, it’s perfectly sane, even modest: a return to a morally responsible standard of animal husbandry. “The animal protection cause simply asks that animals not be treated like things but respected as creatures with inherent rights,” he writes. “It also maintains that we have an ethical responsibility not to abuse them.”'<br /><br />Read the full review, "The Conscience of a Carnivore," on our website:<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.theamericanconservative.com/articles/the-conscience-of-a-carnivore/">http://www.theamericanconservative.co...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="1858757746320869784" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


